,12658,0,'Blend all together in a blender until smooth.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10295,15951,1,'In a blender put ice cubes, chocolate syrup, cherry brandy, vodka, and milk. Blend very well.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10296,14356,1,'Fill glass with ice. Add all liquers. Add milk. shake.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10297,17221,1,'Place the snickers bars in a plastic bag and roll over them with a rolling pin until crushed. Add crushed snickers pieces, ice cream, milk, caramel sauce, chocolate sauce, and chocolate liquor to a blender. Blend until shake is thick and frothy. Pour into glasses and top with chocolate liquor and whip cream.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10298,17220,1,'Blend together in a blender. Serve in a chilled Beer mug with Fresh Blueberries and caramel for topping.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10299,15615,0,'blend liqeuors with ice-cream, milk and syrup. pour into parfait glass, top with whipped cream and garnish with banana and cherry.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10300,14095,1,'Fill a tumbler with ice cubes. Add a shot of Tia Maria and a shot of Jamaican light rum. Fill the tumbler with milk. Blend until smooth and serve immediately.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10301,12688,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10302,12724,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10303,16990,1,'Put 2 shots Godiva Liquour into a glass, add as much or as little milk as you would like.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10304,15639,1,'Blend with Ice until smooth. Serve in a tulip glass, top with whip cream.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10305,16405,1,'Put ice in glass. Pour in shots. Fill with Sour Mix.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10306,14372,1,'Fill Absolut into a glass. Add Lime juice. Add Ice and lime wedges.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10307,14306,1,'Shake and Serve over ice');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10308,16100,1,'Shake sour mix, tequila and amaretto with ice. Strain into highball glass. Add a splash of OJ. Garnish with orange slice and a cherry.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10309,15106,0,'Stirr. Grnish with maraschino cherry.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10310,12710,0,'Throw everything into a blender and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10311,16958,1,'Just mix the two liquids and sprinkle in the cinnamon. Serve either cold or heated.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10312,12708,0,'Juice cantaloupe, pour juice into blender, add banana, and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10313,16986,1,'Mix all ingredients, and pour over ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10314,12668,0,'Mix syrup and milk in a fountain glass. Add soda water, serve with a straw.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10315,12670,0,'Toss strawberries with sugar, and let sit overnight in refrigerator. Cut lemon, reserve two slices. Juice the rest. Mix together the lemon juice, strawberries, apple juice, and soda water. Add slices of lemon (decor, really). In glasses, put ice cubes, and a slice of apple. Pour drink in, and serve.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10316,12672,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10317,12674,0,'Blend til smooth.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10318,12712,0,'Throw everything into a blender and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10319,16275,1,'After pouring in your ingredients, and adding 3-5 ice cubes, according to taste. Stir the drink with a stirrer to get the Vanilla off the bottom.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10320,12720,0,'Juice ginger and lemon and add it to hot water. You may add cardomom.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10321,12714,0,'Throw everything into a blender and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10322,12690,0,'Blend in a blender for 3 seconds. Lassi is one of the easiest things to make, and there are many ways of making it. Basically, it is buttermilk (yoghurt whisked with water), and you can choose almost any consistency that you like, from the thinnest to the thickest. Serve cold.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10323,12698,0,'Put it all in a blender and pour over crushed ice. You can also use other fruits like strawberries and bananas.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10324,12696,0,'Put all ingredients into a blender and blend until nice and frothy. Serve chilled.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10325,12694,0,'Blend the yoghurt and ice cubes together, until the yoghurt becomes more liquid. Add sugar to taste. The lemon/lime is optional but it gives it a slightly tart taste. Dash of salt. Raita is also good for the summer. Instead of having a traditional salad you can make raita instead.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10326,12702,0,'Juice the lemons. Peel and grate the ginger. Place the grated ginger and a liberal dash of the cayenne pepper into a piece of cheesecloth, and tie it into a knot. Let soak in the water. After 15 minutes or so, add the sugar, and the lemon juice. Chill, and serve.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10327,12704,0,'In a large glass, put the lime juice and sugar, and stir well. Add cold seltzer water to fill. Put the lime peels in the glass. Drink. Repeat until limes or soda run out.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10328,12716,0,'Throw everything into a blender and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10329,16995,1,'Pour ingredients over ice and stir.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10330,12718,0,'Throw everything into a blender and liquify.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10331,17167,1,'Pour the raspberry vodka and soda into a highball glass almost filled with ice cubes. Stir well.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10332,12722,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10333,12726,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10334,16967,1,'Blend all ingredients, save nutmeg. Pour into large white wine glass and sprinkle nutmeg on top.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10335,16158,1,'Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth. This makes one drink.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10336,12728,0,'Place all ingredients in the blender jar - cover and whiz on medium speed until well blended. Pour in one tall, 2 medium or 3 small glasses and drink up. Note: Use lots of ice in this one - great on hot days! To add ice: Remove the center of the cover while the blender is on - drop 3 or 4 ice cubs and blend until they''re completely crushed.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10337,12730,0,'Shift the cocoa and sugar together into a medium-sized saucepan. Dissolve the cornstarch in the water, and stir into the cocoa and sugar until it is a smooth paste. Begin heating the mixture, stirring it with a whisk, and gradually pour in the milk. Continue stirring with the whisk as you bring the liquid to a simmer. Allow the chocolate to simmer for about 10 minutes, stirring often, until it is thick, glossy and completely smooth. Serve steaming hot in coffee mug. Serves six.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10338,12732,0,'Boil milk in the top of a deep double boiler five minutes. Remove from fire and add chocolate, mixed with the cinnamon, a little at a time, beating with molinillo or egg beater after each addition. When the chocolate is thoroughly blended, heat to the boiling point. Place over bottom of double boiler and add eggs, whipping constantly, until they are thoroughly blended and the mixture is frothing. Serve in coffee mug. Serves eight.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10339,12734,0,'Melt the bar in a small amount of boiling water. Add milk. Cook over low heat, whipping gently (with a whisk, i would assume) until heated well. Don''t let it boil! Serve in coffee mug.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10340,12736,0,'Heat the cream and milk with the cinnamon and vanilla bean very slowly for 15-20 minutes. (If you don''t have any beans add 1-2 tsp of vanilla after heating). Remove the bean and cinnamon. Add the chocolate. Mix until fully melted. Serve topped with some very dense fresh whipped cream. Serves 1-2 depending upon how much of a glutton you are. For a richer chocolate, use 4 oz of milk, 4 oz of cream, 4 oz of chocolate. Serve in coffee mug.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10341,12738,0,'Melt the chocolate, butter and vanilla in a double boiler. When just smooth stir in the cream.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10342,12744,0,'Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and hot water in 1-quart micro-proof measuring cup (or coffee mug). Microwave at HIGH (100%) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until boiling. Add milk, sitr and microwave an additonal 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until hot. Stir in vanilla, blend well.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10343,12746,0,'Mix with a bit of milk (1 oz or so) in coffee mug. Nuke mug for about 30-50 seconds. Stir until the heated cocoa dissolves. Fill mug with milk. Nuke for 1-2 minutes, depending on wattage and preferences as to burnt mouth parts.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10344,12748,0,'Combine all ingredients in heavy medium saucepan. Stir over low heat until chocolate melts. Increase heat and bring just to a boil, stirring often. Remove from heat and whisk untily frothy. Return to heat and bring to boil again. Remove from heat, whisk until frothy. Repeat heating and whisking once again. Discard orange peel. (Can be prepared 2 hours ahead. Let stand at room temperature. Before serving, bring just to boil, remove from heat and whisk until frothy.) Pour hot chocolate into coffee mugs. Makes 2 servings.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10345,12750,0,'Stir the milk with the chocolate and the cinnamon over low heat until the chocolate dissolves. Add the eggs and beat the mixture until it becomes thick, taking care not to boil. Serve in coffee mug.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10346,15395,1,'Shake ingredients in a mixing tin filled with ice cubes. Strain into a rocks glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10347,17060,1,'Add over ice,shake and pour.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10348,15288,1,'Add both ingredients to shot glass, shoot, and get drunk quick');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10349,13899,1,'put them them in a glass... and slam it to tha head.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10350,13501,1,'Layered in a shot glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10351,14610,1,'Poor in the 151 first followed by the 101 served with a Coke or Dr Pepper chaser.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10352,13807,1,'1. Pour Kahlua into shot glass to about 1/2 full. 2. Using a spoon(inverted), slowly pour in the Peppermint Schnapps until glass is about 3/4 full. Done correctly, the Schnapps will flow under the Kahlua for a clear layer. 3. Again using a spoon, but this time right side up, slowly top off the glass with a layer of Bailey''s. Be careful to place the spoon right at the top of the Kahlua layer and to raise it as the glass fills up. Done correctly, this will provide a layer of Bailey''s floating over the Kahlua. 4. Toss it down all at once for something like a Peppermint Pattie, WITH A BANG!!! NOTE: Best if all ingredients are chilled');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10353,13683,1,'pour into a shot glass and present to consumer, they are expected to cover the top of the shotglass with thier palm, raise the glass, slam it on the bar and the swallow quickly.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10354,16354,1,'Pour all ingredients into shot glass and slam !!!!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10355,17020,1,'Mix in spread glass over ice. Strain and pour in shot glass. Sit down before shotting. ENJOY!!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10356,15853,1,'Layer ingredients into a shot glass. Serve with a stirrer.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10357,13332,1,'Layer the Kahlua, Sambucca and Grand Marnier into a shot glas in that order. Better than B-52');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10358,17079,1,'Pour Kahlua, almost filling shot glass. Then, carefully pour Baileys, using wall of shot glass. This will give the "Guinness" its "head".');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10359,13222,1,'Pour ingredients into 1 ounce shot glass');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10360,13395,1,'Layer in a 2 oz shot glass or pony glass');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10361,13068,1,'Pour Tabasco into bottom of shot glass and fill with tequila.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10362,13066,1,'In a regular-sized shot glass, layer, with a spoon or cherry, the grenadine , the Kahlua , then the Bailey''s Irish cream in equal portions. It goes down really smooth ,and you don''t even need a chaser. It tastes just like chocolate milk.(Really!)');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10363,16998,1,'Pour all ingredients in a mixing tin over ice, stir, and strain into shot glass');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10364,14730,1,'Layer in order into a shot glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10365,14538,1,'This is a layered shot. First pour the Bailey''s into the shot glass. Then take an upside down spoon and touch it to the inside wall of the glass. Carefully add the Kahlua. Repeat this process for the Sambuca. If done properly, the alcohol will stay separated and resemble a bumble bee. Enjoy!!!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10366,13328,1,'Put the milk in the bottom, pour the Liquer on top and add the dash of amaretto. Do not mix. SLAM IT!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10367,14466,1,'This is a layered shot - the Bailey''s must be on top');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10368,13202,1,'Add Amaretto, Bacardi, and vodka. Mix in the Dr. Pepper and beer');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10369,14688,1,'make it an ample size shot!!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10370,17178,1,'Coat the rim of a shot glass with sugar using sugar syrup to stick. Add the Chambord raspberry liqueur to the shot glass, and carefully layer the Baileys Irish Cream on top. Serve.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10371,14956,1,'Boil 3 cups of water then add jello. Mix jello and water until jello is completely disolved. Add the two cups of vodka and mix together. Pour mixture into plastic shot glasses and chill until firm. Then, eat away...');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10372,13775,1,'mix equal parts in pony glass-tastes just like a jelly bean!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10373,17006,1,'Add Kool Aid to a double shot glass, and top with rum. Slam and shoot.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10374,13190,1,'Pour into a large glass with ice and stir. Add a little cranberry juice to taste.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10375,14446,1,'Fill half the shot glass with the kool-aid first. Then put a paper towel over the top of the glass and slowly pour in the vodka. If you do it right, you should be able to see that the two liquids are separated, with the vodka on top. Now slam it! The last thing you''ll taste is the kool-aid.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10376,16196,1,'first you put rhe absinthe, then put tequila, then put the Granadine syrup.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10377,14053,1,'Shake over ice, strain. Serves two.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10378,15330,1,'Add all ingredients to tumbler-Pour as shot');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10379,13198,1,'In a shot glass add 1/3 Kahlua first. Then 1/3 Miduri, topping it off with a 1/3 bailey''s irish cream');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10380,14087,1,'One shot each, shake n shoot');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10381,15082,1,'Pour all the ingredients into tumbler over ice. Strain into glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10382,16985,1,'Pour one part Jack Daneils and one part Jim Beam into shot glass then float Wild Turkey on top.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10383,14602,1,'Fill shot glass with Tequila. Add drops of Tobasco sauce.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10384,15006,1,'Shake with ice and strain into a shot glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10385,16942,1,'Fill glass with rocks, add straw before putting in liquor. Then add the ingredients in order, trying to keep layered as much as possible (i.e. Chambord on bottom, then Vodka, Then soda on top).');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10386,14181,1,'Fill mug almost to top with coffee.Add milk, triple sec and brandy. Stir.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10387,12768,0,'Mix together. Blend at highest blender speed for about 1 minute. Pour into a glass and drink with a straw. Notes: This works best if everything is cold (if you make fresh coffee, mix it with the milk and let it sit in the fridge for 1/2 hour. If it is not frothy, add more milk, or even just some more milk powder. The froth gradually turns to liquid at the bottom of the glass, so you will find that you can sit and drink this for about 1/2 hour, with more iced coffee continually appearing at the bottom. Very refreshing.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10388,15743,1,'fill coffe mug half full of coffee. Fill the other half full of Peach Schnapps. Stir and drink while hot.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10389,16262,1,'Mix the whisky and Baileys Cream in a beer-glass (at least 50 cl). Fill the rest of the glass with coffee.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10390,14782,1,'Combine all ingredients in glass');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10391,12770,0,'Mix together until coffee and sugar is dissolved. Add milk. Shake well. Using a blender or milk shake maker produces a very foamy drink. Serve in coffee mug.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10392,12772,1,'Mix together in a coffee mug and chill before serving.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10393,13971,1,'Heat the coffee, whiskey and sugar; do not boil. Pour into glass and top with cream; serve hot.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10394,15825,1,'Stir the rum, coffee and water together. Top with the whipped cream. Sprinkle with a pinch of well ground coffee and drink with a straw.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10395,16951,1,'Stir. Add whipped cream to the top.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10396,14456,1,'Pour Absolut Kurant into a comfortably big tea-cup. Add the not too hot(!) apple tea and, if you like, some sugar. Enjoy!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10397,12774,0,'Bring 2 cups of water to boil. Add all the ingredients and boil again for about 15 seconds. Let stand for a minute. Warm milk in a pot. Filter tea into cups. Add milk and sugar. That''s IT.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10398,12776,0,'Brew espresso. In a coffee mug, place 1 teaspoon of unsweetened powdered cocoa, then cover a teaspoon with honey and drizzle it into the cup. Stir while the coffee brews, this is the fun part. The cocoa seems to coat the honey without mixing, so you get a dusty, sticky mass that looks as though it will never mix. Then all at once, presto! It looks like dark chocolate sauce. Pour hot espresso over the honey, stirring to dissolve. Serve with cream.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10399,14209,1,'pour 6 oz. of coffee in a mug or Irish coffee cup. add coca mix and chambord, mix well and top off with whipped cream.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10400,12780,0,'Incidentally, a pinch of cinnamon is indeed a nice addition to coffee but true heaven is a cardamom seed. Of course, you serve it in a coffee mug.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10401,14860,1,'Add your GM and then add your coffee.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10402,15515,1,'Mix Coffee, Jack Daniels and Amaretto. Add Cream on top.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10403,12782,0,'Place the coffee and spices in the filter cone of your coffee maker. Brew coffee as usual, let it cool. In a tall glass, dissolve 1 or 2 teaspoons of sugar in an ounce of the coffee (it''s easier to dissolve than if you put it right over ice). Add 5-6 ice cubes and pour coffee to within about 1 inch of the top of the glass. Rest a spoon on top of the coffee and slowly pour whipping cream into the spoon. This will make the cream float on top of the coffee rather than dispersing into it right away.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10404,12784,0,'Prepare a pot of coffee at a good European strength. In the ground coffee, add 2 or 3 freshly ground cardamom pods. Sweeten while hot, then cool quickly. Serve in highball glass over ice, with cream. To get the layered effect, place a spoon atop the coffee and pour the milk carefully into the spoon so that it floats on the top of the coffee.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10405,12786,0,'Combine Thai tea (i.e., the powder), boiling water, and sweetened condensed milk, stir until blended. Pour into 2 tall glasses filled with ice cubes. Garnish with mint leaves. Makes 2 servings.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10406,15328,1,'add all and pour black coffee and add whipped cream on top.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10407,12796,1,'Pare very thinly the bright-colored rind from the oranges (no white). Blot the peel on paper towels to remove any excess oil. Put peel in a 4 cup screw-top jar. Add 2 cups vodka. Close jar. Store in a cool, dark place for 2 days or until the vodka has absorbed the flavor. Remove peel and add remaining vodka. Close jar and add remaining cup of vodka. Close the jar and store in a cool dark place at least 1 month to age.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10408,12798,1,'Combine coffee, sugar and water. Simmer 1 hour and let cool. Add vanilla and vodka. Age in sealed jar 2 to 3 weeks.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10409,12800,1,'Boil water and sugar until dissolved. Turn off heat. Slowly add dry instant coffee and continue stirring. Add a chopped vanilla bean to the vodka, then combine the cooled sugar syrup and coffee solution with the vodka. Cover tightly and shake vigorously each day for 3 weeks. Strain and filter. Its also best to let the sugar mixture cool completely so the vodka won''t evaporate when its added. If you like a smoother feel to the liqueur you can add about 1 teaspoon of glycerine to the finished product.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10410,12802,1,'Place the chopped cranberries in a 2 liter jar that has a tight-fitting lid. Add the sugar and rum. Adjust the lid securely and place the jar in a cool, dark place. Invert the jar and shake it every day for six weeks. Strain the cordial into bottles and seal with corks.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10411,17044,1,'Dissolve sugar in 2 cups of boiling water and add corn syrup. Dissolve the instant coffee in the remaining water. Pour syrup and coffee in a gallon jug. Let it cool. Add vodka and vanilla when cold. For the best result, let the mixture "mature" for 4-5 weeks.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10412,12820,1,'Mix scotch and milk. Add half-and-half. Add rest.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10413,12856,1,'Boil water, sugar and coffe for 10 mins and let cool. Add rum and vanilla. Put in clean bottle(s) and leave for 1 week before using.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10414,16333,1,'Add ice to blender (or to glass if prefer on the rocks) then fruit, and fruite juice depending on personal prefference then add the Rum, Vodka, Tequila, and triple sec. blend till smooth, rim glass with sugar or salt and pour mixture in. garnish with lemon or lime slice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10415,12862,0,'Add 1/4 cup water to ginger root. Boil 3 minutes. Strain. Add the liquid to the guava, lemon and pineapple juices. Make a syrup of sugar and remaining water. Cool. Combine with juices and pineapple. Chill throroughly.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10416,16202,1,'Fill the blender with 3/4 ice. Add sweet & sour mix to the top of the ice. Add about 1" of pineapple juice, 1/2" of melon liqeur, and 1/2 to 1/4" of amaretto. Then blend the mix until it is of margaritta consistency or thinner.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10417,12864,0,'If you use the whole all spice and cloves, tie them in cheesecloth. Heat the mixture. Stir occasionally. If you want an alcoholic drink, rum would be nice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10418,16289,1,'Chill both ingredients!! Mix in a tumbler and enjoy!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10419,15849,1,'Pour all ingrediants into a large punch bowl. Add ice and 4 oranges that are peeled and divided.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10420,14622,1,'Fill glass with ice and fish, add vodka, grape soda and orange juice. DO NOT STIR!!!!! Serve well chilled.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10421,14364,1,'Mix all ingredients in a pitcher. Mix thoroughly and pour into whatever is available, the bigger the better! This drink packs a big punch, so don''t over do it.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10422,12890,0,'Combine first four ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved, chill. Then add ginger ale just before serving. Add ice ring to keep punch cold.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10423,12910,0,'In a small mixer bowl beat egg yolks till blended. Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating at high speed till thick and lemon colored. Stir in milk, stir in rum, bourbon, vanilla, and salt. Chill thoroughly. Whip cream. Wash beaters well. In a large mixer bowl beat egg whites till soft peaks form. Gradually add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Fold yolk mixture and whipped cream into egg whites. Serve immediately. Sprinkle nutmeg over each serving. Serve in a punch bowl or another big bowl. NOTE: For a nonalcoholic eggnog, prepare Eggnog as above, except omit the bourbon and rum and increase the milk to 3 cups.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10424,12916,0,'Whip egg substitute and sugar together, combine with the two kinds of milk, vanilla, and rum. Mix well. Chill over night. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 6 servings.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10425,12914,0,'In large saucepan, beat together eggs, sugar and salt, if desired. Stir in 2 cups of the milk. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick enough to coat a metal spoon and reaches 160 degrees F. Remove from heat. Stir in remaining 2 cups milk and vanilla. Cover and regfigerate until thoroughly chilled, several hours or overnight. Just before serving, pour into bowl or pitcher. Garnish or add stir-ins, if desired. Choose 1 or several of: Chocolate curls, cinnamon sticks, extracts of flavorings, flavored brandy or liqueur, fruit juice or nectar, ground nutmeg, maraschino cherries, orange slices, peppermint sticks or candy canes, plain brandy, run or whiskey, sherbet or ice-cream, whipping cream, whipped. Serve immediately.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10426,12944,0,'Boil sugar and spices in water, leave in the water for 30 minutes. Strain the spiced water and mix with the wine. Heat slowly until short of boiling temperature. (To remove alcohol, let it boil for a while.) You may add lemon or orange juice to taste. Serve in irish coffee cup.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10427,12954,0,'Take a bunch of grape juice and a bunch of fizzy stuff (club soda, ginger ale, lemonlime, whatever). Mix them in a punch bowl. Take orange sherbet and lime sherbet. Scoop out scoops and float them in the punch, let them melt a little so that a nasty film spreads all over the top of the punch but there are still "bubbles" in it in the form of sherbet scoops. Looks horrible, tastes just fine.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10428,13254,1,'Combine vodka and ginger beer in a highball glass filled with ice. Add lime juice. Stir gently. Garnish.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10429,16041,1,'Add all contents to a large jug or punch bowl. Stir well!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10430,12988,1,'Simmer 3 cups water with, sugar, cloves, cinnamon sticks, and lemon peel in a stainless steel pot for 10 minutes. Add wine heat to a "coffee temperature" (DO NOT BOIL) then add the brandy.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10431,17191,1,'Pour all ingredients, except the bitters, into shaker filled with ice. Shake well. Pour into large glass, filled with ice. Add Angostura bitters, "on top". Garnish with cocktail cherry and pineapple.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10432,14978,1,'Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl and serve.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10433,16250,1,'Mix all ingredients in glass & add ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10434,13020,1,'Mix all together in a pitcher and refrigerate. Add cloves and cinnamon sticks to taste. Serve in wine glasses.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10435,13026,1,'Mix wine, sugar and fruit, and let sit in the fridge for 18-24 hours. The mixture will have a somewhat syrupy consistency. Before serving stir in brandy and cut the mixture with soda water until it have a thinner, more wine like consistency. Serve from a pitcher in wine glasses.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10436,17141,1,'Throw it all together and serve real cold.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10437,13032,0,'Combine peach nectar, orange juice and brown sugar in a large saucepan. Tie cinnamon and cloves in a small cheesecloth bag. Drop into saucepan. Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Simmer 10 minutes. Stir in lime juice. Serve in hot mugs.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10438,13036,0,'Throw everything into a blender and mix until fairly smooth. Serve over ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10439,13042,0,'Combine all ingredients in a punch bowl.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10440,13024,1,'Dissolve the sugar in hot water and cool. Peel the citrus fruits and break into wedges. Mix the wine, sugar syrup, fruit, and Fresca in a pitcher and put in the fridge for a few hours. Serve in tall glasses with a straw.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10441,13056,0,'Mix wine and soft drink. Pour into glass. Add ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10442,13058,1,'Combine all of the ingredients and pour over a block of ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10443,14594,1,'Pour 5cl of Cointreau on ice, add 2cl of fresh lemon (or lime) juice, stir gently, and finally add slices of lemon/lime in glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10444,15423,1,'Drop shooter in glass. Fill with beer');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10445,13282,1,'Fill pint glass half full with Bass. Next pour Guiness over a spoon slowly until glass is full. If done correctly the Guiness will stay on top and the Bass on bottom hence the name Black & Tan.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10446,16403,1,'CAREFULLY to avoid explosive head formation: Pour Beer glass half full of favorite rootbeer and top off with Guinness.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10447,17035,1,'Pour the corona into an 18oz beer glass pour the bacardi limon into the beer stir very gently');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10448,16047,1,'Use a 15 oz glass. Add Campari first. Fill with beer.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10449,17065,1,'Pour the Corona into an 18oz beer glass pour the rum into the beer.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10450,13128,1,'Pour the lager first then add the blackcurrant cordial. Top up with the cider. The colour sholud be very dark approaching the colour of Guiness.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10451,17015,1,'Add the ingredients in the order listed in the recipe. Care must be taken when adding the Guinness to prevent an excess of foam. Do Not add ice.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10452,15086,1,'Open the Corona. Fill the empty space in the neck in the bottle with the rum. The bottle should be filled to the top. Plug the bottle with your thumb or the palm of your hand. Turn the bottle upside-down so the rum and beer mix. Turn the bottle rightside-up, unplug, and drink.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10453,14378,1,'Fill a pint glass almost full with beer. Then fill the rest with orange juice (careful not to fill it to the top). Then take the shot of Amaretto and drop it in.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10454,13389,1,'Pour ingredients into a pint glass. Drink. Fall over.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10455,15789,1,'Put blackcurrant squash in first up to about 1cm in glass. Then add the larger and cider one after another.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10456,14510,1,'Blend ingredients for 30 seconds. Definitely refreshing for a hot summer''s day !');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10457,16447,1,'Scoop two large scoops of vanilla ice-cream into frosted beer mug. Next, add 2 ounces Maker''s Mark. Then, pour in coke. Gently stir and enjoy.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10458,17135,1,'Pour half of coke in a glass. Then add Bacardi and top it off with the remaining coke. Stir and drink up!');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10459,17108,0,'Take a glass, pour the Coke in the glass, then you take 7 drops of lemon juice. Granish with a lemon slice on the rim of the glass.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10460,14482,1,'There are many good cherry liqueurs you can use, but I prefere Heering. Add one share of the liqueur. Then you add one share of Soda. For a sour sling use Tonic (most people prefer the drink without Tonic). Afterwards you fill the glass with Orange Juice and ice cubes.');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10461,15933,1,'Mix sambuca with rootbeer and stir. Add ice');INSERT INTO COCKTAIL_RECIPES (recipe_id, cocktail_id, is_alcoholic, cocktail_details) VALUES (10462,15691,1,'No specific mixinginstructions, just poor every ingredient in one glass. The lemon goes with it.');